Interesting to see this decentralized internet work.

I see that this site gives you the ability to edit your post.

Is anyone new and interested in this Zeronet thing?

It's supposed to be similar to Bit torrent,  not reliant on central servers.

I have websites that I don't have online any more.  You could just put your old websites online with this system.  I might do that,  have the old data put out there, free, uncensored.

It's interesting.

http://oxwugzccvk3dk6tj.onion/qresearch/index.html


FYI about 8chan on Tor / Onion.

In case you're wondering where most of the people are

That link requires a Tor browser.

>>35f68968-47dd-4d5e-a17d-b61a1fdb3d2d

Hugely Notable and something we really really need.

The largest communications platforms on the internet can be viewed as public utilities, perhaps?

No censorship. The old phone companies didn't listen to your phone calls and cut you off as a customer because they didn't like your ideology.

>>c5f8a8e9-f03e-4715-a273-6d531cf8f93e

Is this a concern?

If someone knows the IP address that my ISP has assigned to my computer, that person still has no idea that IP address = me.

This isn't facebook, where they put your name on everything.

I should be concerned about this, because?
